chunk_content: • Newly Tested and/or Referred for Testing: Persons within each priority population type for P R whom HIV testing is indicated because they do not know their HIV status or their last HIV- E negative test was more than 3-6 months ago (or more/less frequently as indicated by National V Guidelines) should either be offered an HIV test on site or given an HIVST for primary use. An E N individual who receives an HIVST kit should also receive information about who to contact or a T clinic to visit for confirmatory testing should the HIVST have a reactive result. Note: Persons who I O access testing and whose results are newly tested HIV-positive in the reporting period should also N be counted under “newly tested” even if they return for additional prevention services during that reporting period.
